					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12967879#post-4489409</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-12967879/scp-3193#post-4489409</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 04 Feb 2020 17:43:23 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Dyslexion</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5549954</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>While I was writing the logs, I was unsure whether I wanted to give a conclusive ending to their story. But I can give you a couple of ideas.</p> <p>1. They both sacrificed themselves.<br /> An arrow to your chest is a pretty dangerous thing. Without proper medical care, you could die pretty quickly. And since there's no &quot;debrief&quot; with Jack, (or Julie) you could reasonably assume that he died fighting whatever was in that control room.</p> <p>2. They were both treated for their injuries, amnesticized, and released.<br /> This is a pretty cut and dry response. Standard operating procedure.</p> <p>3. They were recruited.<br /> This is also a pretty viable answer. Even without training, they're both very resourceful. And since this isn't a one-time incident, you'd want experienced people who are immune to 3193 assisting in containment.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
